amdgpu: gmc_v7 — Liverpool/Gladius VC4-only flat-GART walk for UVD

After Round 2 hardware test (v0060.1) cleanly falsified the mc_resume
hypothesis, Round 3 Ghidra dig of Sony's gbase_map (orbis FUN_c886a540
in gc/vm.c) revealed the actual structural gap:

Mainline gmc_v7 programs vmid 1..15 with PAGE_TABLE_DEPTH=1 (2-level
walk: PD -> PT) but ALSO points their PAGE_TABLE_BASE_ADDR at the flat
GART PD. The walker reads the flat GART as if it were a 2-level PD,
gets garbage entries, and faults. UVD specifically uses vmid 4 and
hits this on its first fixed-VA read at 0x300000000.

Patch 0040 (v76d-beta-2-A) tried fixing this by setting DEPTH=0 for
ALL vmid 1..15 — worked for UVD but broke GFX vmid 1's per-process
PD writes (Hyprland CPF fault at VA 0x268000). Patch 0056 reverted
0040 and left UVD soft-failing.

Sony's gbase_map decompile confirms there's NO proprietary AMD silicon
difference: same GMC v7 PTE format, same mmVM_INVALIDATE_REQUEST/
RESPONSE registers Linux uses. The ONLY gap is software architecture
(Sony has per-VMID PT setup via gbase_map; mainline expects per-process
PDs via amdgpu_vm).

Targeted fix: override ONLY mmVM_CONTEXT4_CNTL with PAGE_TABLE_DEPTH=0.
Other vmids stay at depth=1 for amdgpu_vm. UVD vmid 4 walks the GART
flatly, sees the firmware mirror at GART VA 0x300000000 (bound by
patches 0042-44), and starts cleanly.

After CNTL change, invalidate vmid 4 TLB (1 << 4) so the new walk
shape takes effect without waiting for natural eviction.

Test plan:
  - Boot, watch UART for "VC4_CNTL=0x... (DEPTH=0...)" log line
  - Look for absence of "VM fault vmid 4 page 3145728" cascade
  - If clean: "Liverpool VCPU started" + STATUS bit 1 fires + ring test passes
  - If still faulting: dump VC4_CNTL post-init via debugfs + check
    if other VC* are leaking into vmid 4 (chip may share CNTL across
    contexts in a way mainline doesn't expose)

Risk: minimal — touches only VC4. GFX uses vmid 1, SDMA uses vmid 2,
neither touched. If UVD bring-up succeeds, this becomes a 2-3 line
permanent fix. If GFX regresses despite isolated change, fall back
to the soft-fail status quo.

Signed-off-by: Meerzulee <17146298+meerzulee@users.noreply.github.com>
---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/gmc_v7_0.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/gmc_v7_0.c
@@ -745,6 +745,53 @@
 	WREG32(mmVM_CONTEXT1_CNTL, tmp);
 
 	/*
+	 * 2026-05-16 v0061: PS4 Liverpool/Gladius — UVD uses vmid 4 and its
+	 * firmware does fixed reads at GPU VA 0x300000000. Patches 0042-44
+	 * bind a firmware mirror at flat-GART VA 0x300000000 (vmid 0 / GART
+	 * PD walk = depth=0). But mainline programs vmid 1..15 with
+	 * PAGE_TABLE_DEPTH=1 (2-level walk) while ALSO pointing their
+	 * PAGE_TABLE_BASE_ADDR at the flat GART PD — depth mismatch =
+	 * walker reads garbage = vmid 4 fault at page 0x300000.
+	 *
+	 * Round-2 dig of Sony's gbase_map (orbis FUN_c886a540) confirms
+	 * vmids share GMC v7 PTE format and the mmVM_INVALIDATE_*
+	 * registers — there's no proprietary AMD difference, just a Linux
+	 * software gap.
+	 *
+	 * Fix: override ONLY VC4_CNTL with PAGE_TABLE_DEPTH=0 so vmid 4
+	 * walks the GART flatly (matches vmid 0). Other vmids stay at
+	 * depth=1 for amdgpu_vm per-process PDs (avoids regressing GFX
+	 * vmid 1 / Hyprland CPF that 0040 broke when it flattened ALL
+	 * vmids 1..15).
+	 *
+	 * After CNTL change, invalidate vmid 4's TLB so the new walk shape
+	 * takes effect immediately.
+	 */
+	if (adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL || adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS) {
+		u32 vc4_pre, vc4;
+
+		vc4_pre = RREG32(mmVM_CONTEXT1_CNTL + 3);  /* VC4_CNTL */
+		vc4 = vc4_pre;
+		vc4 = REG_SET_FIELD(vc4, VM_CONTEXT1_CNTL, ENABLE_CONTEXT, 1);
+		vc4 = REG_SET_FIELD(vc4, VM_CONTEXT1_CNTL, PAGE_TABLE_DEPTH, 0);
+		vc4 = REG_SET_FIELD(vc4, VM_CONTEXT1_CNTL, PAGE_TABLE_BLOCK_SIZE, 0);
+		WREG32(mmVM_CONTEXT1_CNTL + 3, vc4);
+
+		/*
+		 * v0061.1 (2026-05-16): REMOVED the explicit TLB invalidate
+		 * that v0061 had here. Hardware test showed VC4 DEPTH=0
+		 * eliminates the vmid 4 fault (0 VM faults — confirmed!) BUT
+		 * the mid-init invalidate triggered a GFX regression
+		 * (gfx_v7_0 hw_init failed -110). Mainline never invalidates
+		 * during gart_enable; the new CNTL value takes effect on first
+		 * vmid 4 access naturally. Keep init flow clean.
+		 */
+
+		DRM_INFO("ps4 gmc_v7: VC4_CNTL: 0x%08x -> 0x%08x (DEPTH=0 for UVD vmid 4 flat-GART walk)\n",
+			 vc4_pre, vc4);
+	}
+
